history.text: Hi
Are you there?
This movie is called Catch Me if you Can.
Does it sound good?
It received a rating of 96% on Rotten Tomatoes
Do you know who was in it?
No I dont. Who was in it?
Leonardo DiCaprio, Tom Hanks, Christopher Walken, Amy Adams, and Nathalie Baye
It is a American bigraphical crime film
Sounds interesting. Is it a drama? or more of a comedy?

A critical respons said "Catch Me if You can" never takes itself or its subjects too seriously, and contains more genuinely funny material than about 90% of the so-called "comedies" found in multiplexes these days
This movie was directed by Steven Spielberg
Actually sounds pretty good. I think I would be interested in seeing that.
Steven Spielberg is a good director
Yes, this movie received a CinemaScore of A-
A critical response was, "This is not a major Spielfberg film, although it is an effortlessly watchable one"
You know a movie is good when even the bad reviews are good :)
This sounds really cool I will definitely have to check this move out.
Yes, all the ratings on this movie were ok
there were two key scenes
What were they?
I'll tell you about them
Please do :)

One is when the father is denied a business loan from a bank. the wife has an affair with the friend of her husband. the son poses as a sub in his French class. The son's parents file for divorce, and the son runs away. The son reles on confidence scams to get by.
Sounds pretty interesting
I can definitely see that being funny
or at least interesting enough to be worth watching
Another scene shows how the son starts to work for the bank fraud department of the FBI
Sounds really good. I will definitely try to see it! Thanks for the info
The ending credits reveal the son is married, has a family, and has caught some of the most elusive money forgers
You're welcome.
You should really see the movie
I really will try it actually does sound good
Love leo dicap
The Metacritic score is 76/100
Cya :)

uid1response.feedback: The user I was talking to described the movie well and ti sounded pretty interesting. It seemed comedic and different, not just your run of the mill story line that isn't innovative. It made me want to see how he went from forging checks to catching forgers while working for the FBI.
